Grosvenor May Start Buying Listed Company Shares, Telegraph Say

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-09-25T05:53:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/grosvenor-may-start-buying-listed-company-shares-telegraph-say.html
Grosvenor Group Ltd. may start
buying shares in listed companies, the Sunday Telegraph
reported, citing Jeffrey Weingarten, chief executive of the
company’s fund management unit.  Grosvenor will announce a new U.S. fund this week,
according to the report. The company, which owns estates in
 London ’s Mayfair and Belgravia, will focus on  Tokyo , London and
 Washington , the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
 cairlie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  